%N A392966 Number of ordered rooted trees with non-root node weights summing to n. Such that non-root nodes are each labeled with a subset s of [n], the weight of a node is the number of elements in s, only non-root nodes labeled with singleton subsets can have child nodes, and the labels of a given tree form a set partition of [n].
%F A392966 E.g.f.: A(x) satisfies A(x) = 1 + A(x)*(exp(x) + x*A(x) - x - 1).
%F A392966 E.g.f.: 2 / (2+x-exp(x) + sqrt((2+x-exp(x))^2 - 4*x)). - _Seiichi Manyama_, Mar 12 2026
%e A392966 a(2) = 5 counts:
%e A392966     o        o         o       o     o
%e A392966     |       / \       / \      |     |
%e A392966   {1,2}   {1} {2}   {2} {1}   {1}   {2}
%e A392966                                |     |
%e A392966                               {2}   {1}
%o A392966 (PARI) D_x(N) = {my(x='x+O('x^(N+1))); Vec(serlaplace((-(exp(x)-2-x) - sqrt((exp(x)-2-x)^2-4*x))/(2*x)))}
%Y A392966 Cf. A000108, A000670, A052895.
%K A392966 nonn,easy
%O A392966 0,3
